+# Tao mechanism map to candidate circuit object
+
+[VERIFIED] Tao's delayed-transfer mechanism, as reconstructed in the local library, is the five-role chain
+
+```text
+carrier A -> clock B -> trigger C -> conduit D -> next carrier A_next,
+```
+
+with the load-bearing reduced shell monomials
+
+```text
+A*A -> B,
+A*A -> C,
+B*C -> C,
+A*C -> D,
+C*D -> A,
+A*B -> A,
+A*C -> A,
+D*A_next -> D,
+D*D -> A_next.
+```
+
+[CHECKED] The exact NS candidate object should therefore be organized around a role-level directed 3-uniform hypergraph `G_target` whose edges are the Tao monomials above, not just the coarse topological chain. The chain alone is too weak: Phase 1 needs to know which exact triads are intended and which are spectators.
+
+[CHECKED] Role map:
+
+| Tao role | Shell variable | Exact object in preferred definition | Mechanism role |
+| --- | --- | --- | --- |
+| `A` | `X1,n` | helical packet `P_A` | current carrier |
+| `B` | `X2,n` | helical packet `P_B` | slow clock / gate opener |
+| `C` | `X3,n` | helical packet `P_C` | tiny trigger and later amplifier target |
+| `D` | `X4,n` | helical packet `P_D` | conduit / rotor leg |
+| `A_next` | `X1,n+1` | helical packet `P_A_next` | next carrier |
+
+[VERIFIED] Exact NS interaction law to be used later:
+
+```text
+∂t û(k) + ν|k|^2 û(k) = -i Σ_{p+q=k} (q · û(p)) P_k û(q),
