+## Rejected alternative 1: one exact mode per Tao role
+
+[CHECKED] This fails before coefficient calculations.
+
+- `A,A -> B` and `A,A -> C` cannot both hold with distinct single target modes, because one exact ordered pair of wavevectors has one sum.
+- `B,C -> C` would require `k_B + k_C = k_C`, hence `k_B = 0`.
+- `A,B -> A` would require `k_B = 0`.
+- `D,A_next -> D` would require `k_A_next = 0`.
+
+[CHECKED] Therefore a literal five-conjugate-pair circuit is not even a candidate exact object. Any honest exact definition must packetize the Tao roles.
+
+## Rejected alternative 2: energy-only or signed-net leakage
+
+[CHECKED] A leakage metric based only on net energy flux, or on signed sums of monomials, is too weak.
+
+- Large spectator channels can cancel at one instant while still being structurally present.
+- Tao's mechanism is sign- and threshold-sensitive at the amplitude level, not just at the energy-flux level.
+- Phase 1 will produce monomial-level exact ledger entries; the leakage notion must live at that same granularity.
+
+[CHECKED] For this reason the preferred `Leak(u)` uses absolute monomial magnitudes relative to intended target drive.
