+| `D` | `X4,n` | helical packet `P_D` | conduit / rotor leg |
+| `A_next` | `X1,n+1` | helical packet `P_A_next` | next carrier |
+
+[VERIFIED] Exact NS interaction law to be used later:
+
+```text
+∂t û(k) + ν|k|^2 û(k) = -i Σ_{p+q=k} (q · û(p)) P_k û(q),
+P_k = I - (k ⊗ k)/|k|^2,
+û(-k) = overline{û(k)}.
+```
+
+[CHECKED] In helical variables, this becomes an exact scalar triad sum
+
+```text
+(∂t + ν|k|^2) u_s(k)
+  = Σ_{p+q=k} Σ_{sp,sq} C^{s,sp,sq}_{k,p,q} u_sp(p) u_sq(q),
+```
+
+where `C^{s,sp,sq}_{k,p,q}` is the exact Waleffe/Leray geometric coefficient. This is the right Phase 1 language because it exposes signs, helicities, and target-by-target monomials without any toy-model averaging.
+
+# Preferred definition
+
+[CHECKED] Preferred definition: a `near-closed Tao circuit` is a tuple
+
+```text
+NCTC = (S, {P_A, P_B, P_C, P_D, P_A_next}, G_target, Θ, u|I)
+```
+
+with the following exact data and admissibility parameters.
+
+## Exact data
+
+[CHECKED] `S` is a finite helical support:
+
+- `S` consists of finitely many exact helical modes `(k,s)` with `k != 0`.
+- `S` is sign-closed in the real-field sense: if `(k,s)` is active then `(-k,-s)` is active as its forced mirror.
+
+[CHECKED] The packets `P_A, P_B, P_C, P_D, P_A_next` partition `S`.
+
+- Each packet may contain multiple conjugate pairs.
+- Packets are exact subsets of `S`, not approximate wave packets and not shell averages.
+
+[CHECKED] `G_target` is the role-level target hypergraph
+
+```text
+E_target =
+{
+  A,A -> B;
+  A,A -> C;
+  B,C -> C;
+  A,C -> D;
+  C,D -> A;
+  A,B -> A;
+  A,C -> A;
+  D,A_next -> D;
+  D,D -> A_next
+}.
+```
+
+[CHECKED] Each role-level edge must be witnessed by at least one exact helical triad
+
+```text
+(p,sp),(q,sq) -> (k,s)  with  p + q = k,
+```
+
+whose source modes lie in the source packets and whose target mode lies in the target packet named by the edge.
+
+[CHECKED] For an exact state `u` supported on `S`, define the target drive of an edge `e = R1,R2 -> R3` by
+
+```text
+Drive_e(u)
+  := Σ | C^{s,sp,sq}_{k,p,q} u_sp(p) u_sq(q) |,
+```
+
+where the sum runs over all exact helical triads realizing that role edge with
+
+- `(p,sp) in P_R1`,
+- `(q,sq) in P_R2`,
+- `(k,s) in P_R3`,
+- `p + q = k`.
+
+[CHECKED] Define
+
+```text
+Drive_target(u) := Σ_{e in E_target} Drive_e(u).
+```
+
+[CHECKED] Define internal spectator leakage by
+
+```text
+Leak_in(u)
+  := Σ | C^{s,sp,sq}_{k,p,q} u_sp(p) u_sq(q) |,
+```
+
+summed over all exact helical triads with sources in `S` and target in `S` that do not belong to any role edge in `E_target`.
+
+[CHECKED] Define external spectator leakage by
+
+```text
+Leak_out(u)
+  := Σ | Σ C^{s,sp,sq}_{k,p,q} u_sp(p) u_sq(q) |,
+```
+
+summed over every target helical mode `(k,s)` with `k` generated by some pair of source modes in `S` but with `(k,s) not in S`.
+
+[CHECKED] The scalar leakage functional is
+
+```text
+Leak(u) := (Leak_in(u) + Leak_out(u)) / Drive_target(u),
+```
+
+provided `Drive_target(u) > 0`.
+
+[CHECKED] Why this scalarization is the right one:
+
+- It is computable directly from an exact Phase 1 ledger.
+- It is role-sensitive: it compares intended monomials against unintended monomials, not just total energy.
+- It is conservative: the absolute values refuse to hide large spectators behind fine-tuned cancellations.
+
+## Admissibility parameters
+
+[CHECKED] `Θ` is a user-chosen tolerance vector
+
+```text
+Θ = (η_leak, η_seed, Γ_amp, Γ_rot, Γ_hand, θ_pre, θ_act, Δ_act, ρ_next),
+```
+
+with
+
+- `0 < η_leak < 1` a leakage budget,
+- `0 < η_seed < 1` the allowed tiny-seed ratio,
+- `Γ_amp, Γ_rot, Γ_hand > 1` target dominance ratios,
+- `0 < θ_pre < θ_act` pre-trigger and activation thresholds for the trigger packet,
+- `Δ_act > 0` the maximum activation-window length,
+- `ρ_next > 1` the required next-carrier growth factor during activation.
+
+[CHECKED] These are not exact NS objects. They are admissibility parameters chosen before the Phase 1 audit.
+
+## Witness interval and dominance conditions
+
+[CHECKED] Let `u|I` be an exact NS solution segment on `I = [t0, t2]`, and evaluate the role packets relative to the chosen finite support `S`.
+
+[CHECKED] This tuple is a near-closed Tao circuit of tolerance `Θ` if there exists a trigger time `t1 in (t0,t2)` such that:
+
+1. Pre-trigger regime on `[t0,t1)`:
+
+```text
+Leak(u(t)) <= η_leak,
+||u|_{P_C}(t)||_2 <= θ_pre ||u|_{P_A}(t)||_2,
+Drive_{D,D->A_next}(u(t)) <= η_seed Drive_{A,A->B}(u(t)).
+```
+
+2. Hierarchy conditions on `[t0,t2]`:
+
+```text
+Drive_{A,A->C}(u(t)) <= η_seed Drive_{A,A->B}(u(t)),
+Drive_{B,C->C}(u(t)) >= Γ_amp Drive_{A,A->C}(u(t)),
+Drive_{A,C->D}(u(t)) >= Γ_rot (Leak_in(u(t)) + Leak_out(u(t))),
+Drive_{D,D->A_next}(u(t)) >= Γ_hand (Leak_in(u(t)) + Leak_out(u(t)))
+```
+
+whenever the relevant target drives are active.
+
+3. Activation window on `[t1,t2]`:
+
+```text
+t2 - t1 <= Δ_act,
+||u|_{P_C}(t1)||_2 >= θ_act ||u|_{P_A}(t1)||_2,
+||u|_{P_A_next}(t2)||_2 >= ρ_next ||u|_{P_A_next}(t1)||_2.
+```
+
+[CHECKED] This definition is deliberately modest. It does not smuggle Tao's exact engineered coefficients into exact NS. It only asks for:
+
+- one exact support,
+- one target ledger,
+- one leakage budget,
+- one dominance hierarchy,
+- one delayed-trigger orbit segment.
+
+# Backup definition or rejection of alternatives
+
+[CHECKED] No backup definition is retained. The following plausible alternatives fail the precision gate and should not be carried into Phase 1.
+
+## Rejected alternative 1: one exact mode per Tao role
+
+[CHECKED] This fails before coefficient calculations.
+
+- `A,A -> B` and `A,A -> C` cannot both hold with distinct single target modes, because one exact ordered pair of wavevectors has one sum.
+- `B,C -> C` would require `k_B + k_C = k_C`, hence `k_B = 0`.
+- `A,B -> A` would require `k_B = 0`.
+- `D,A_next -> D` would require `k_A_next = 0`.
+
+[CHECKED] Therefore a literal five-conjugate-pair circuit is not even a candidate exact object. Any honest exact definition must packetize the Tao roles.
+
+## Rejected alternative 2: energy-only or signed-net leakage
+
+[CHECKED] A leakage metric based only on net energy flux, or on signed sums of monomials, is too weak.
+
+- Large spectator channels can cancel at one instant while still being structurally present.
+- Tao's mechanism is sign- and threshold-sensitive at the amplitude level, not just at the energy-flux level.
+- Phase 1 will produce monomial-level exact ledger entries; the leakage notion must live at that same granularity.
+
+[CHECKED] For this reason the preferred `Leak(u)` uses absolute monomial magnitudes relative to intended target drive.
+
+# Precision gate analysis
+
+## Notation table
+
+[CHECKED]
+
+| Symbol | Meaning | Type |
+| --- | --- | --- |
+| `S` | finite sign-closed helical support | exact NS object |
+| `P_A, P_B, P_C, P_D, P_A_next` | Tao role packets partitioning `S` | exact NS objects |
+| `G_target` | role-level target hypergraph with Tao monomials | exact NS object |
+| `C^{s,sp,sq}_{k,p,q}` | exact helical/Leray coefficient for `p+q=k` | exact NS object |
+| `Drive_e(u)` | target-drive magnitude for role edge `e` | exact computed functional |
+| `Leak_in(u)` | unwanted in-support monomial mass | exact computed functional |
+| `Leak_out(u)` | forced out-of-support emission mass | exact computed functional |
+| `Leak(u)` | `(Leak_in + Leak_out)/Drive_target` | exact computed functional |
+| `η_leak, η_seed` | leakage / tiny-seed budgets | user tolerances |
+| `Γ_amp, Γ_rot, Γ_hand` | dominance thresholds | user tolerances |
+| `θ_pre, θ_act` | delayed-trigger thresholds | user tolerances |
+| `Δ_act, ρ_next` | activation-window / next-carrier requirements | user tolerances |
+
+## Exact objects versus user tolerances
+
+[CHECKED] Exact NS objects:
+
+- the finite support `S`,
+- the packet partition,
+- the exact helical coefficients,
+- the exact target and spectator triad lists,
+- the functionals `Drive_e`, `Leak_in`, `Leak_out`, `Leak`.
+
+[CHECKED] User-chosen admissibility parameters:
+
+- `η_leak`, `η_seed`,
+- `Γ_amp`, `Γ_rot`, `Γ_hand`,
+- `θ_pre`, `θ_act`,
+- `Δ_act`, `ρ_next`.
+
+[CHECKED] This separation is clean enough for Phase 1: the ledger computes the exact objects; the theorem or obstruction statement later compares them to whichever tolerance vector the user commits to.
+
+## Why the precision gate passes
+
+[CHECKED] The preferred definition is concrete enough to be true or false because each clause reduces to one of:
+
+- exact triad arithmetic,
+- exact helical coefficient lookup,
+- a finite monomial ledger sum,
+- a finite list of threshold inequalities on an exact solution segment.
+
+[CHECKED] No phrase such as "mostly isolated" survives unquantified. It has been replaced by the explicit witness `Leak(u) <= η_leak`.
+
+[CHECKED] Delayed-trigger logic is also no longer slogan-level. It is represented by:
+
+- a pre-trigger threshold `θ_pre`,
+- a trigger-crossing threshold `θ_act`,
+- a finite activation window `Δ_act`,
+- a concrete next-carrier growth test `ρ_next`.
+
+## What would count as a positive obstruction
+
+[CHECKED] A Phase 1 or Phase 2 positive obstruction would be any theorem or exhaustive exact audit showing that for every admissible finite packet support intended to realize `G_target`, at least one of the following always happens:
+
+- one of the target role edges in `G_target` has no exact triad witness,
+- `Leak(u)` has a support-independent lower bound above the admissible `η_leak`,
+- the required hierarchy `η_seed`, `Γ_amp`, `Γ_rot`, `Γ_hand` cannot hold simultaneously,
+- the delayed-trigger conditions force a zero mode or equivalent forbidden degeneracy,
+- the activation window cannot be separated from spectator growth.
+
+## What would count as a counterexample / near-circuit construction
+
+[CHECKED] A Phase 1 or Phase 2 counterexample would be an explicit finite support `S`, explicit packet partition, explicit helicities, and an exact NS solution segment `u|I` for which every clause in the preferred definition holds for a stated tolerance vector `Θ`.
+
+## Unexpected findings
+
+[CHECKED] The first exact obstruction is more basic than the earlier coefficient-rigidity story: several Tao monomials are not even representable with one mode per role. Packetization is forced already by exact wavevector arithmetic.
+
+[CHECKED] This does not kill the strategy. It changes the minimal search object from "five modes" to "five packets on a finite helical support."
+
+# Phase 1 recommendation or stop verdict
+
+[CHECKED] Recommendation: proceed.
+
+[CHECKED] Phase 1 should audit the preferred definition in the exact helical decomposition, not in a coarser shell or packet model. The packets should be used only to assign Tao roles; every ledger entry should still be an exact helical triad with its exact coefficient and exact source/target packet labels.
+
+[CHECKED] Minimal Phase 1 representation:
+
+- use exact helical decomposition of a finite Fourier support closed under sign,
+- keep packet labels `A, B, C, D, A_next`,
+- enumerate every exact triad with both inputs in `S`,
+- classify each triad as target or spectator relative to `G_target`,
+- compute `Drive_e`, `Leak_in`, and `Leak_out` symbolically before any dynamics.
+
+[CHECKED] The first Phase 1 subproblem should be a minimal packet-cardinality audit, because the naive five-conjugate-pair picture is already dead. The audit should start from the smallest sign-closed packet support that can realize all nine role edges in `G_target` without invoking a zero mode.
+
+[VERIFIED] Primary-source anchors used for the exact language:
+
+- Tao, "Finite time blowup for an averaged three-dimensional Navier-Stokes equation," JAMS 29 (2016), DOI `10.1090/jams/838`.
